Ayah bot — third-party content notice
=====================================

The Quran text used by this project is the Uthmani text from the Tanzil
project (https://tanzil.net). It was downloaded with `pnpm data:fetch`
and is stored, unchanged, at:

    prisma/data/quran-uthmani.json

Tanzil Quran Text
Copyright (C) 2007-2024 Tanzil Project
License: the Tanzil terms of use (https://tanzil.net/docs/tanzil_license)

In short, the Tanzil terms allow you to copy and share the Quran text
without change, as long as you:

  - do not modify the text in any way,
  - clearly state Tanzil as the source, and
  - link back to https://tanzil.net.

This project does all three. The text is treated as read-only data: it is
verified on download (6236 ayat, correct count per surah) and is never
edited by application code.


Tafseer (commentary)
--------------------

A subscriber chooses which tafseer they receive (see
src/database/reference/tafseers.ts). Each edition is downloaded with
`pnpm data:fetch:tafseer` from an authoritative source, verified on download
(6236 entries, correct count per surah, every entry non-empty), reproduced
unchanged, and attributed to its publisher. Each is used for non-commercial
educational purposes (helping people understand and memorize the Quran), and
none is edited by application code.

  - التفسير الميسر (Al-Tafsir Al-Muyassar) — the concise tafseer of the King
    Fahd Complex for the Printing of the Holy Quran (مجمع الملك فهد لطباعة
    المصحف الشريف). From the AlQuran.cloud API (edition "ar.muyassar").
    Copyright (C) King Fahd Complex for the Printing of the Holy Quran.
    Stored at prisma/data/tafseer-muyassar.json

  - المختصر في التفسير (Al-Mukhtasar) — the concise tafseer of the Tafsir
    Center for Quranic Studies (مركز تفسير), published in the King Fahd
    Complex's Noble Quran Encyclopedia. From the QuranEnc API (edition
    "arabic_mokhtasar"). Copyright (C) Tafsir Center for Quranic Studies.
    Stored at prisma/data/tafseer-mukhtasar.json

  - تفسير السعدي (Tayseer al-Karim ar-Rahman) by Abd ar-Rahman as-Sa'di.
    From the Quran.Foundation API (the data behind quran.com, edition
    "ar-tafseer-al-saddi"); its HTML is converted to plain text on download.
    Stored at prisma/data/tafseer-saadi.json

  - تفسير ابن كثير (Tafsir Ibn Kathir) by Ibn Kathir. This edition is long
    (tens of thousands of characters per ayah), so — like the recitation audio
    — its full text is NOT stored or redistributed here: only a bounded opening
    (one message) is committed, and the bot links to the full text for that
    ayah on quran.com. From the Quran.Foundation API (edition
    "ar-tafsir-ibn-kathir"). Stored (opening only) at
    prisma/data/tafseer-ibnkathir.json

The per-ayah "read in full" links the bot builds, and the live sources above,
are checked by `pnpm verify:tafseer`.

Recitation audio
----------------

The daily ayah's optional recitation audio is the standard Mushaf Murattal
recordings of the reciters listed in src/database/reference/reciters.ts
(among them Mahmoud Khalil Al-Husary, Mohamed Siddiq Al-Minshawi, Abdul Basit
Abdul Samad, Mishary Rashid Alafasy, Maher Al-Muaiqly, and Saad Al-Ghamdi). The
audio is fetched per ayah from everyayah.com and is NOT stored or redistributed
in this repository; only the URLs are referenced, and Telegram caches each clip
after the first send. Each recording remains the work and property of its
reciter and original publisher, used here for non-commercial educational
purposes (helping people learn and memorize the Quran). No audio is modified.

